Multiply or divide inputs. Choose element-wise or matrix product and specify one of the following:

Break a feedback loop involving data signals between function-call blocks.
For loops involving parent and child function-call blocks (i.e., where the initiator of the child function-call block is inside the parent function-call block), place this block on the feedback signal from the child to the parent in order to ensure that the signal''s value does not change during the execution of the child.
For loops involving function-call blocks connected to branches of the same function-call signal, this block latches the signal at the input of the destination function-call block, and thereby allows it to execute prior to the source function-call block. 
Such latching results in the destination block reading a delayed signal from the previous execution of the source function-call block.

message.entry: The Manual Variant Source provides variation on the source of a signal. Blocks connected to the input ports define variant choices and one input port is active during simulation. Blocks connected to the inactive ports will be removed from the simulation. Double-clicking the block icon selects the active choice which is shown with a line connecting the input to output.

The Manual Variant Sink provides variation on the sink (destination) of a signal. Blocks connected to the output ports define variant choices and one output port is active during simulation. Blocks connected to the inactive ports will be removed from the simulation. Double-clicking the block icon selects the active choice which is shown with a line connecting the input to output.

The Variant Connector provides variation of physical elements. Blocks connected to the variant side (square in the icon) define a variant choice that is part of the simulation when the variant control expression evaluates to true. There are two methods for defining the variant choice: \n1. Leaf region. Connector type: leaf. In this case all blocks connected to the variant side will be conditional.\n2. Bounded region. Connector type: primary coupled with one or more Variant Connector blocks set to nonprimary. In this case, multiple Variant Connector blocks with the same connector tag form a bounded variant region.
